393
00:21:24,430 --> 00:21:27,194
-Let go of the damn ring.
-This ain't right.

394
00:21:28,634 --> 00:21:30,295
Write a letter to the editor.

395
00:21:30,336 --> 00:21:34,466
Oop. I forgot.
I own the newspapers.

396
00:21:34,506 --> 00:21:36,974
We'll take care of everything.

397
00:21:37,009 --> 00:21:38,738
Get him out of here.

398
00:21:38,777 --> 00:21:40,108
Don't you worry,
Mr. Fairbanks.

399
00:21:40,145 --> 00:21:42,636
This is a good ring.

400
00:21:42,681 --> 00:21:45,309
This is a very nice ring.

401
00:21:48,454 --> 00:21:51,446
All right, just hear me out, OK?
One more time.

402
00:21:51,523 --> 00:21:54,083
I just feel if we were
to go back, you know...

403
00:21:54,159 --> 00:21:57,219
and, uh, give him
a chance to confess...

404
00:21:57,296 --> 00:21:58,627
you know, come clean...

405
00:21:58,664 --> 00:22:03,829
he might just hand over what is
in fact my rightful property.

406
00:22:03,869 --> 00:22:06,360
I could see how that sounds
all messed up, right?

407
00:22:06,405 --> 00:22:07,599
Comin' out of my mouth.

408
00:22:07,640 --> 00:22:09,471
But it's the truth.

409
00:22:09,508 --> 00:22:11,635
Can I see my lawyer?

410
00:22:11,677 --> 00:22:14,009
Seventeen,
with the robbery suspect...

411
00:22:14,046 --> 00:22:16,071
at Twenty-five Harbor Heights,
Marblehead...

412
00:22:16,115 --> 00:22:17,639
what's your twenty?

413
00:22:18,651 --> 00:22:21,142
Yeah. That's it, 10-4. We're on
the corner of Camden and 4th...

414
00:22:21,186 --> 00:22:23,211
